<br>
What are everyone's goals for the guild? <br>
Do we want to see it grow at the expense of familiarity<br>
between members, or would we prefer to keep it small and <br>
tight? If the latter, we're on the right track. If the former, on<br>
to a new question: Does anyone have suggestions for how to<br>
broaden our player base? Short of /ooc'ing in PoK &quot;Colossus<br>
looking for members!&quot; anyway.<br>
<br>
I think originally we intended Colossus to be<br>
something of a raiding guild. I don't think we've really &quot;raided&quot;<br>
in a month or more. Dunno when the WR points were last<br>
updated. The limiting factor is not our gear or our epics or<br>
even our levels... it's just number of people. I'm not sure on<br>
this but I think we have fewer active members now than we<br>
did the day Colossus was formed.<br>
<br>
Just thought it was time for an update in our idea of Colossus.<br>
<br>
Please post your thoughts.<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
Teir <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub199.ezboard.com/bcolossusoflanys.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eqteiresias>EQTeiresias</A> at: 6/7/03 6:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub199.ezboard.com/bcolossusoflanys.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jsbcody>jsbcody</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#330000>(6/8/03 1:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub199.ezboard.com/fcolossusoflanysfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Your goals for the guild</span><hr size=1> Yes some people have left or have retired, or don't have the time to play right now. I think we may need to expand, but within reason and limits. No, shouting in PoK is not a good idea. Yes I would like to keep the &quot;family&quot; feeling I enjoy in the guild, so I guess each and every one of us will have to do some recruiting. That is probably the best way to expand with minimum amount of pain and discomfort. There are certain classes that we need if we wish to become a self sufficient raiding guild. We have tanks, a slower, a chanter, a cleric, and DPS galore. We need a druid (like I told Zev, who would have thought-druids ARE useful), a wizard, a rogue, and then maybe a few back-ups for the real important classes. This would greatly expand our raiding abilities, ie. having back ups when some people can't attend, so raids wouldn't be called or changed. The number needed for this would be 25 to 30 in guild.<br>
<br>
I have noticed that when we raid, people who attend are VERY IMPRESSED with our guild. <br>
<br>
I don't like the idea of &quot;raiding&quot; other guilds for people because the good ones will always be reluctant to leave. If they weren't, I don't think we would be interested in them. <br>
<br>
I hope I have made some sense, it is late at night as I type this, and this just some thoughts on this subject. <br>
<br>
Laalyn Wolfhart<br>
&quot;Insane&quot; Ranger of Colossus<br>
